It is set to 'Discharged' when capacitors voltage is too l";
CM_ SG_ 2527679773 DLM_BFS_SwitchRequest "Indicates the internal unlatch request status from switch pression.
None (no unlatch request)
No Unlatch (unlatch requested but non foreseen by software)
Single Pull (when a unlatch with singel pull is performing)
Wait for second press (when a double ";
CM_ SG_ 2527679773 DLM_BFS_SystemError "It shall be set to:
No Fault (when no fault is detected)
Peripheral Fail(internal/external handle switch, CDL/DL/COM lines, WDSM Fail, Pydos fail)
SuperCap Supply (when super cap supply is switched on and CAN is running)
Internal Fault 
(microcontrol";
CM_ SG_ 2527679773 DLM_BFS_WDSMActuationsBFS "It carries the information of how many actuations (either from user or actuator test) have been made in the lifespan of the other (driver) side WDSM. In case of DLM replacement, this backup value will be read from the other DLM and written.";
CM_ SG_ 2527679773 DLM_BFS_WDSMActuationsResetTrig "Trigger sent by the replaced DLM in order to ask the other (driver) side DLM to send the backup value of WDSM actuations. Value is then internally restored";
CM_ SG_ 2527679773 DLM_BFS_WDSMStatus "Signal is set to 'Life Cycle Expired' when a prefixed time is elapsed from the WDSM installation with its basic setting.
It is set to 'Discharged' when capacitors voltage is too low.
'Life Cycle Expired' state has priority over 'Discharged'
WDSM replac";
CM_ SG_ 2527679773 DLM_BFS_WDSMTrigger "Signal is set to 1 when basic setting for WDSM installation date storing is called. Signal returns to 0 after a key cycle, passenger side";


CM_ SG_ 2527679772 DLM_FS_DoorStatus "Door state from latch state sensoring reading, driver side. Set to invalid when a fault to latch sensoring is detected";
CM_ SG_ 2527679772 DLM_FS_GenericFailure "It informs about SmartLatch error state, driver side 
If DTCs are supported, this fault flag is basically informing that at least one DTC is set.";
CM_ SG_ 2527679772 DLM_FS_LatchStatusFeedback "Latch locking status feedback, driver side";
CM_ SG_ 2527679772 DLM_FS_ProductionMode "Set to 'Active' when production mode is Active, driver side";
CM_ SG_ 2527679772 DLM_FS_SuperCapStatus "It shall be set when a determined life time (first trial value: 15 years) has been elapsed. After that, supercap functionality is always guaranteed but with degraded performances, driver side.
It is set to 'Discharged' when capacitors voltage is too low";
CM_ SG_ 2527679772 DLM_FS_SwitchRequest "Indicates the internal unlatch request status from switch pression.
None (no unlatch request)
No Unlatch (unlatch requested but non foreseen by software)
Single Pull (when a unlatch with singel pull is performing)
Wait for second press (when a double ";
